你却没做到
You couldn't do that.

44
00:01:43,320 --> 00:01:45,520
什么都做不了
You can't do anything.

45
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:47,440
你会为我能做的事而惊讶
You'll be surprised what I can do.

46
00:01:49,240 --> 00:01:51,040
保安 306病房
Security, room 306.

47
00:01:53,440 --> 00:01:54,880
斯蒂芬 你...
Stephen, just...

48
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,360
走吧
Just go.

49
00:01:59,080 --> 00:02:01,840
走吧... 等... 再回来
Just...go and come back when...

50
00:02:09,480 --> 00:02:12,680
斯蒂芬... 斯蒂芬...
Stephen... Stephen...

51
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:15,080
斯蒂芬
Stephen!

52
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:20,080
四号房
Number four.

53
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:24,440
到了 哈瑞特・斯通 一样的药 却没症状
There we go. Harriet Stone. Same drugs, no symptoms.

54
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:27,160
一整批都有毒怎么她还能没事
How did she remain immune if it was a poison batch?

55
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:28,680
她没聋
She's not deaf.

56
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:31,120
为何不进来问她呢
Why don't you come in and talk to her?

57
00:02:33,960 --> 00:02:37,920
- 书好看吗... 哈瑞特 - 有点悲伤
- So, is it a good book...Harriet? - Hmm, a little sad.

58
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:40,880
- 是吗 - 是 不过没事 我喜欢悲伤的
- Is it? - Yes, but that's all right, I like sad.

59
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:43,480
- 是啊 悲伤也挺好的 不是吗 - 是
- Yeah, sad's all right, isn't it? - Yeah.

60
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:46,280
- 对书来说 还有音乐 - 是
- In books anyway. And tunes. - Hmm, yes.

61
00:02:47,480 --> 00:02:48,720
还有什么
So, what else?

62
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:52,080
关于苏珊娜还有什么想说的
What else can you tell us about Susanna?

63
00:02:52,160 --> 00:02:54,360
- 她不开心 - 不开心吗
- She's not happy. - No?

64
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:58,800
- 为什么 - 我也不知道原因 直觉而已
- Why not? - I don't know why, I just know.

65
00:02:58,880 --> 00:03:00,760
她帮你拿药
She gives you your medication?

66
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:02,920
药挺好的 是啊
For all the good it does. Yes.

67
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:07,880
- 你是法国人 - 是的
- Are you French? - Yes.

68
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:13,080
我很想再去一次法国
I'd love to go to France again.

69
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:14,760
但不可能了
But I never will.

70
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:17,111
是的 可能旅游对现在的你来说
No, the journey would probably be

71
00:03:17,112 --> 00:03:17,760
太困难了
too difficult for you now.

72
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:22,000
喂
Yep.

73
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:26,400
苏珊娜・博蒙特在医院
Susanna Beaumont's in hospital.

74
00:03:26,480 --> 00:03:28,940
可怜的苏
Oh, poor Suze.

75
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:33,040
她朗读的声音很好听
She has a lovely reading voice, you know?

76
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:34,800
我不知道你想说什么
I don't understand your point.

77
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:35,680
她自己说
She said herself

78
00:03:35,681 --> 00:03:37,480
她没希望再去法国了
it was unlikely she would see France again.

79
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:39,000
- 所以你赞同了 - 是
- And you agreed? - Yes.

80
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:40,360
但是也许她不想...
But maybe she didn't want...

81
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:42,720
不好意思 你是觉得她还能再去法国吗
I'm sorry, do you think she will see France again?

82
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:44,400
不是 但那不是重点
No, but that's not the point.

83
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:45,983
你为何不直接说
Why didn't you just say,

84
00:03:45,984 --> 00:03:48,560
"你都快进棺材了 奶奶"
"You'll be in the graveyard soon, Grandma."

85
00:03:48,640 --> 00:03:51,120
因为我没这样想
Because it's not what I was thinking.

86
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:54,640
有时你只用说好话 警察
Sometimes you just need to say the right thing. Police.

87
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:56,720
不要说永远 类似这样的
Never say never, that kind of thing.

88
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:58,720
那应该会说出很白痴的话
That would have been a really dumb thing to say.

89
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:00,842
好吧 苏珊娜・博蒙特
Okay. Susanna Beaumont.

90
00:04:00,843 --> 00:04:03,200
给她打了镇定剂 还是很难受
She's sedated, still in a lot of pain.

91
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:05,386
还有 今天早上他兄弟来了
And there was a bit of a scene this morning

92
00:04:05,387 --> 00:04:06,520
